11.23.22  7:21 pm   you've done it again.
could you tell us what sort of "decisions" you make when writing a script?

     how does it go, what should i do or not do, etc

     what's your "process"?

     figure out how it goes

     what are you "looking" for?

     first prize

     what are you trying to "express"?

     some of the feelings and dynamics at play in our world

     you've mentioned writing ten-minute-long scripts before. do you plan to produce them any time soon?

     sure, if i am brave

     how do these longer narratives play out?

     see things, places, people thinking and talking, ..... connections and references to things that happened earlier, .... pondering what could happen later.... etc

     would you ever be willing to post a narrative that is transmitted solely through text, as opposed to the audio/video stuff you do? or are the audio and video too important for you to ever eschew?
thanks

     i've been known to eschew various things from time to time
